    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This test has not failed on `main` since May 30th. The linked failure is a PR branch run. I do not see any obvious reason it failed. \r\n\r\n@dannykopping since this has not happened on `main` and the only branch it has occurred is the notifications branches, can I close this? It it appears on `main` we can just reopen with more evidence.\r\n\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-07-08 12-01-46](https://github.com/coder/coder/assets/5446298/81633f4d-7324-4f43-b150-ce2dc4376eec)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nI am unsure why this is failing, but some things I found.\r\n\r\n- It only fails on `test-go-race` test in the last 3 months on `main`.\r\n- It does not fail on `main` very often. Last failure dates:\r\n```\r\nMay 30 19:10:51.000\r\nMay 08 19:11:18.000\r\nMay 07 19:10:12.000\r\nMay 02 19:11:19.000\r\nApr 30 19:08:39.000\r\nApr 19 19:07:39.000\r\nApr 16 19:08:11.000\r\nApr 12 19:07:10.000\r\n```\r\n\r\n- On some PR branches it has some failures, but I did not investigate if they were total test failures, or specifically this test.\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nSource\r\n\r\nhttps://app.datadoghq.com/ci/test-runs?query=test_level%3Atest%20%40test.name%3A%22TestTemplateVersionsArchive%2FArchive-Unarchive%22%20%40test.status%3Afail&agg_m=count&agg_m_source=base&agg_t=count&currentTab=overview&eventStack=&fromUser=false&index=citest&start=1712681708805&end=1720457708805&paused=false",
